'''Shyster''' may refer to:

* ([[description]]) A '''shyster''' is someone who acts in a disreputable, unethical or unscrupulous way, especially in the practice of law and politics, or a [[con artist]]. The term -- possibly because of its vaguely Yiddish sound --  is sometimes mistaken to connote Jewishness. That connotation, however, is correct as far as the denoted meaning of the word. The word probably originated from the carnival game "Coconut Shy," given the reputation carnival workers and their games have. Other possible origins include a real 19th-century New York lawyer named Scheuster, or possibly from German ''Scheisser'' - "incompetent worthless person," literally "defecator". This term has been used in [[Isaac Asimov]]'s short science-fiction robot story "Evidence". An atmosphere is created around a falsity and then proven wrong.
* ([[military]]) '''SS-3 Shyster''' is the [[NATO reporting name]] for the [[R-5]] [[theatre ballistic missile]].

